description: Odfjell SE provides services for the transportation and storage of bulk liquid chemicals, acids, edible oils, and other specialty products in North America, South America, Norway, the Netherlands, rest of Europe, the Middle East, Asia, Africa, and Australasia. It operates through Chemical Tankers and Tank Terminals segments. The company owns and operates chemical tankers that offer global and regional transportation; and tank terminals, which provide storage of various chemicals and petroleum products. As of December 31, 2024, it operated through a chemical tanker fleet of 71 vessels, including 46 owned/leased, 4 operational bareboat, 14 time chartered, and 3 pool vessels. The company's terminal network consists of 459 tanks with 1.3 million cubic meters of storage capacity. Odfjell SE was incorporated in 1914 and is headquartered in Bergen, Norway.
